Sirota’s hiring as a senior adviser and speechwriter was announced by the Sanders campaign on Tuesday morning after The Atlantic contacted the campaign and inquired about the undisclosed role Sirota held while attacking other Democrats.
Faiz Shakir, Sanders’s campaign manager, confirmed in an interview on Tuesday afternoon that Sirota had been in an advisory role prior to his hiring on March 11.
Read: Bernie Sanders is the Democratic front-runnerThe online fury of Sanders’s supporters was one of the most defining characteristics of his 2016 campaign.
On Monday night, after being contacted for a second time by The Atlantic with a list of specific questions about his undisclosed work for Sanders, Sirota did not respond to the email but deleted more than 20,000 tweets.
He did post a photo on Twitter of himself bowling on Monday evening, wearing a turkey hat.